A Curry Chicken Recipe I like
2023-10-21
robert arno saalbach
A nice and easy recipe for curry chicken that I make semi regularly and is also great to share with friends.
curry-chicken-recipe
Recipe
-
<h2>Ingredients (for 4)</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Rice
	<li>One Tablespoon of Butter
	<li>600g of Chicken
	<li>3+ (to your liking) toes of Garlic
	<li>Onion
	<li>200g Cream Cheese
	<li>Curry Powder
	<li>Chili Powder
	<li>Paprika
	<li>Tomatoes
	<li>250ml of Coconut Milk
	<li>Pepper and Salt
</ul>
<br><br><br>
<h2>Recipe, Step-by-Step</h2>
<p>0. Prepare a separate pot with rice and let it cook until ready.</p>
<p>1. Prepare a deep pan, or even pot. Place it on medium to high heat and put the tablespoon of butter into it.</p>
<p>2. (Season your chicken first). Put in the 600g of Chicken and cook for ca. 2min.</p>
<p>3. Add the onion, and let cook with the chicken for around 2-3min. (Don''''t forget to mix).</p>
<p>4. Add garlic and let cook with the rest for about 1 min.</p>
<p>5. Add the cream cheese and make sure it melts and gets on everything.</p>
<p>6. Then add as much Curry and Chili Powder as you like, and make sure to mix everything up.</p>
<p>7. Add the tomatoes and the paprika and let the entire mass cook for a few minutes.</p>
<p>8. At this point add the 250ml of coconut milk.</p>
<p>9. Finish off by adding pepper and salt to your liking, then combine with the rice and serve warm.</p>
<br><br>
<p>Enjoy!</p>
